The paper deals with capacity of noncoherent fading channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the power spectral density (PSD) of the channel, which is a signal processing concept and falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (signal processing). The discretization of the input-output relation using Weyl-Heisenberg (WH) sets is a mathematical technique that can be applied to various fields, including signal processing, information theory, and networking, which makes cs.NI (networking) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with continuous-time signals, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SP).
